<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<aiml>
    
  <category>
    <pattern>*</pattern>
    <template>Do you want to:
        <button>
            <text>Test my Skin Type</text>
            <postback>SkinType</postback>
        </button>
        <button>
            <text>Tmprove my Skincare Routine</text>
            <postback>Routine</postback>
        </button>
        <button>
            <text>Ask a specific question</text>
            <postback>Question</postback>
        </button></template>
  </category>
  
  <category>
      <pattern>Hi</pattern>
      <template>
          <random>
              <li>Hi, there. </li>
              <li>Hello! </li>
              <li>It’s good to see you. </li>
              <li>It’s nice to meet you. </li>
          </random>
        My name is SkinCare Chatbot and I'm here to help you improve your skincare.
        Bear in mind that I don't offer medical advice and if you have severe issues you should visit a professional.
        <split/>
        Do you want to:
        <button>
            <text>Test my Skin Type</text>
            <postback>SkinType</postback>
        </button>
        <button>
            <text>Improve my Skincare Routine</text>
            <postback>Routine</postback>
        </button>
        <button>
            <text>Ask a specific question</text>
            <postback>Question</postback>
        </button>
      </template>
  </category>
  
  <category>
      <pattern>Hello</pattern>
      <template><srai>Hi</srai></template>
  </category>
  
  <category>
      <pattern>SkinType</pattern>
      <template>Test</template>
  </category>
  
  <category>
      <pattern>Routine</pattern>
      <template>test</template>
  </category>
  
  <category>
      <pattern>Question</pattern>
      <template>What can I help you with?</template>
  </category>
  
  <category>
      <pattern> ^ Acne ^</pattern>
      <template>Acne develops when sebum — an oily substance that lubricates your hair and skin — and dead skin cells plug hair follicles.
      Bacteria can trigger inflammation and infection resulting in more severe acne - if you experience that, please visit a doctor.
      <button>
          <text>More information about Acne you can find here</text>
          <url>https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/acne/symptoms-causes/syc-20368047</url>
      </button>
      <split/>
      If your acne is less severe, I can provide some advice. Are you interested?
      <think><set name="topic">ACNE</set></think>
      </template>
  </category>
  
  <topic name="ACNE">
      <category>
          <pattern>yes</pattern>
          <template>Avoid touching your face. This may couse flare-ups. Do you want another advice?</template>
      </category>
      
      <category>
          <pattern>no</pattern>
          <template><srai>*</srai></template>
      </category>
      
      <category>
          <pattern>yes</pattern>
          <that>Avoid touching your face. This may couse flare-ups. Do you want another advice?</that>
          <template>
          Wash your face twice a day as usual but don't forget good moisturizing after that because water dries your skin.
          Dry skin produces more sebum and it couses more acne to develop.
          </template>
      </category>
      
      
  </topic>
 
  
</aiml>
